{
  "texts": [
    "EVT and Representativity category addresses methods to ensure measurements taken during analysis represent future operational scenarios accurately.",
    "Santinelli et al. [78] propose a method that involves applying EVT to execution time measurements to estimate the WCET.",
    "They aim to model the tails of the execution time distribution to predict the probability of extreme execution times, thereby providing a statistically grounded estimate of the pWCET.Davis et al. [51] discuss HYPTA methods too.",
    "HYPTA integrates elements of both static and measurement-based approaches to provide more accurate pWCET estimates.",
    "HYPTA leverages the strengths of static analysis in understanding the structural aspects of programs and the empirical accuracy of measurement-based techniques."
  ]
}